n a limited extent as a way to avoid the terrible and unpredictable effects of wars. Violent Alternatives to War: Justifying Actions Against Contemporary Terrorism engages in a moral discussion of the challenges associated with violent alternatives to war when confronting terrorism and suggests a comprehensive approach to how this form of violence can be legitimized and how it ought to be used against this contemporary threat.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aTerrorismxPreventionxMoral and ethical aspects. 4aGerechter Krieg. 4aTerrorismus. 4aTerrorismusbekämpfung. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Terrorism.2bisacsh  aAlternatives to War.  aJust War Theory.  aPolitical Violence.  aTerrorism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2022 Part 1z978311076682008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2021 Englishz978311075417908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2021z9783110753943oZDB-23-PLW0 cEPUBz97831107300050 cprintz978311073128640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311072989440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110729894423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110729894/original  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075417-9  EBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-076682-0  DG Plus DeG Package 2022 Part 1b2022  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-PLWb2021